==English==
===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-swig.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɪɡ|-ɪɡ]]

===Verb===
'''to swig''' ([[swigged]], swigged)

# To [[drink]] (usually by [[gulp]]ing or in a [[greedy]] or unrefined manner).
#: ''The drunken sailor '''swigged''' from the bottle of whisky.''
# To take up the last bit of slack in rigging by taking a single turn around a cleat, then hauling on the line above and below the cleat while keeping tension on the line   (jargon: rigging, either of sailing ships or lifting)

===Noun===
'''swig'''

# a [[drink]]
#:''He took another '''swig'''.''

